-Nobody forced you to come here,

05:49.849 --> 05:53.227
Oh, then drag me out,
Tell the security to throw me out,

05:53.311 --> 05:54.395
Don't spoil my mood, please,

05:54.479 --> 05:55.813
So, ladies and gentlemen,

05:55.897 --> 06:00.568
it would be nice for me to invite
His Excellency, the Executive Governor,

06:00.651 --> 06:06.532
who has supported and also enjoyed
the tremendous support of women,

06:06.616 --> 06:11.537
to join the celebrant and her friends
on the dance floor,

06:11.621 --> 06:18.044
Please let's welcome His Excellency
Akinwale Razaq Onikoyi,

06:18.127 --> 06:21.339
Please can we make some noise
for his Excellency?

06:21.422 --> 06:23.633
[applause]

06:23.716 --> 06:26.719
[music, singing continues]

06:58.584 --> 07:03.005
KT! Dude, your party is bumping, man,

07:04.757 --> 07:06.634
Are you sure it's not time
we go down to join them?

07:07.385 --> 07:11.055
Oh, you're welcome to,
but you're on your own,

07:11.139 --> 07:15.726
Is that not Governor Onikoyi?
And look at this man laughing and relaxed,

07:16.144 --> 07:18.688
Maybe I should go and pitch him
one of my top-notch ideas,

07:19.480 --> 07:24.026
Man, Kitan, Look, your mum
has all these crazy connects

07:24.110 --> 07:25.611
and you waste them,

07:26.529 --> 07:29.365
It's not your fault,
when lack of problem is your problem,

07:29.657 --> 07:31.242
Have you guys seen Kemi tonight?

07:32.869 --> 07:37.039
Yo, dude, your sister is fine,

07:37.123 --> 07:38.374
[laughs]

07:38.666 --> 07:39.834
Whose sister?

07:39.917 --> 07:40.960
[woman clears throat]

07:45.548 --> 07:47.425
Mum was looking for you,

07:53.973 --> 07:54.974
Whose mum?

07:55.600 --> 07:58.519
Your mum or my mum?

07:58.603 --> 08:00.062
Fine, Kitan,

08:00.771 --> 08:03.399
It would be great
if you came downstairs to help

08:03.483 --> 08:06.819
your mum receive guests
and celebrate her birthday,

08:06.903 --> 08:11.073
[MC] A loving mother
to two lovely children

08:11.157 --> 08:14.035
and the mummy of the whole community!

08:14.118 --> 08:16.496
That's what we call her,
At least, ladies and gentlemen,

08:16.579 --> 08:20.541
at this point, please permit me
to welcome to the microphone,

08:21.250 --> 08:24.921
the celebrant, for a few words,

08:25.004 --> 08:29.258
Please let's put our hands together for,,,

08:29.342 --> 08:31.552
KT, must you be such a jackass to her?

08:31.636 --> 08:35.932
[MC] She's Mrs, Eniola Salami, My mummy!

08:36.015 --> 08:38.351
-The mother of the whole community,
-[applause]

08:41.770 --> 08:43.397
Oh, what can I say?

08:49.654 --> 08:51.197
Thank you very much,

08:51.822 --> 08:52.949
Oh, my God,

08:53.533 --> 08:56.244
Thank you for coming everybody, I--

08:58.204 --> 09:01.207
[whispering, inaudible]

09:02.375 --> 09:05.586
Yes, as I was saying,
thank you so much for coming,

09:05.670 --> 09:07.713
Well, I don't know how to make speeches,

09:08.798 --> 09:13.344
But I know it's not easy to gather people
on a Tuesday for a party,

09:14.303 --> 09:16.305
You honor me and may God honor you all,

09:16.889 --> 09:21.227
Thank you so much, There's so much to eat
and so much to drink,

09:21.310 --> 09:23.896
Thank you, once again,
Be merry with me, please,

09:23.980 --> 09:26.274
-[whooping]
-[applause]

09:27.149 --> 09:29.110
[MC] The celebrant, ladies and gentlemen!

09:30.027 --> 09:31.779
Kemi, take care of my guests,

09:32.154 --> 09:36.242
It's never a party without good music,,,

09:37.827 --> 09:43.791
from the most versatile band,
in the whole of Africa,

09:44.709 --> 09:46.419
Akin Shuga and the Shuga Band,

09:46.502 --> 09:48.421
I hope you people
have not forgotten your promise,

09:48.504 --> 09:52.258
[MC] And I wanna tell you guys,
if you're still sitting down,,,

09:52.341 --> 09:54.343
Senator, my mother
didn't get where she is today

09:54.427 --> 09:56.387
by breaking her promises,

09:56.887 --> 10:01.017
There's been no official appointment yet,
so until then, we wait,

10:01.642 --> 10:03.269
That's fine, that's fine,

10:03.352 --> 10:07.023
But I just want to remind you
that a deal is a deal

10:07.106 --> 10:09.567
and it won't be good if you break it,

10:09.650 --> 10:10.735
Remind?

10:12.194 --> 10:14.488
With all due respect, Senator,

10:14.572 --> 10:18.993
you of all people should know that
my mother doesn't take kindly to threats,

10:19.577 --> 10:22.622
I'd be mindful not to
tug the tail of the lion if I were you,

10:23.456 --> 10:27.627
We will get to you after the announcement
has been made, as promised,

10:28.294 --> 10:31.464
So until then, Senator,
try to stay out of danger,

10:32.381 --> 10:36.969
After all, Lagos can be
a very dangerous city,

10:37.053 --> 10:40.890
as you and your family must know,
Enjoy the rest of the party, sir,

10:46.729 --> 10:48.731
[music continues]

11:00.951 --> 11:03.204
[man whimpering] Boss, please,

11:17.176 --> 11:18.177
Stand him up,

11:19.720 --> 11:21.597
-[whimpering]
-Stand up,

11:30.064 --> 11:31.065
[in Yoruba]
Look at me,

11:33.234 --> 11:34.485
Look at me!

11:38.989 --> 11:40.282
Have you eaten?

11:44.787 --> 11:46.580
[in English]
Nasco, why?

11:49.083 --> 11:50.668
Are we barbarians here?

11:50.751 --> 11:52.253
[in Yoruba]
What's all that rubbish?

11:54.171 --> 11:55.256
Please don't be offended,

11:56.882 --> 11:58.801
[in English]
I apologize on their behalf,

11:59.218 --> 12:01.595
Sometimes, they don't know
how to treat a friend,

12:04.014 --> 12:06.058
[in Pidgin]
You're my friend, right?

12:07.726 --> 12:09.145
[in Yoruba]
We are friends?

12:11.272 --> 12:13.023
Very good,

12:18.362 --> 12:19.697
[in Yoruba]
Who sent you?

12:19.780 --> 12:24.368
[no audible dialogue]

12:24.452 --> 12:25.870
I said, who sent you?

12:28.664 --> 12:31.834
Boss, please, They will kill me,

12:31.917 --> 12:36.255
Really? So you think I'm the one here
to play games with you?

12:37.465 --> 12:40.092
[in English]
I'm going to ask you for the last time,

12:42.136 --> 12:46.891
Who sent you people to kidnap
Chief Davies' daughter?

12:47.391 --> 12:49.435
Please have mercy, Boss,

12:53.981 --> 12:55.941
I hate when people waste my time,

13:01.197 --> 13:02.239
Clear the mess,

13:07.453 --> 13:08.662
Aha, boys,

13:11.499 --> 13:15.127
[in Yoruba] Ade Tiger will bring
your food and drinks, Okay?

13:16.420 --> 13:18.172
Rice or Eba?

13:18.255 --> 13:19.798
Either one, Boss,

13:20.216 --> 13:21.717
How about pounded yam?

13:22.343 --> 13:24.845
[in English]
Good job, Well done, boys,

13:26.889 --> 13:28.224
Sort this out,

13:33.562 --> 13:36.982
[woman speaking Yoruba]
What more do you want from me?

13:37.066 --> 13:39.652
You're a stupid woman!
I said you're a stupid woman!

13:41.570 --> 13:42.905
Get out of here!

13:42.988 --> 13:46.242
-[woman] Leave me alone!
-[man] I will deal with you!

13:46.325 --> 13:49.161
[woman]
You won't even let me feed well,

13:50.955 --> 13:52.748
[woman] Eniola!

13:52.831 --> 13:54.959
[continues screaming]

13:59.004 --> 14:01.340
[woman in Yoruba]
It's okay I met you this way,

14:01.423 --> 14:04.385
What they said about you
is who you really are,

14:04.468 --> 14:09.014
King, please help me,
This insult is becoming unbearable,

14:09.848 --> 14:12.935
I called the police, they did nothing,

14:13.727 --> 14:17.898
My daughter's boyfriend
impregnated her and denied it,

14:17.982 --> 14:21.110
Please have mercy on me,
Help me fix this, please,

14:21.193 --> 14:23.112
Please help me,

14:25.614 --> 14:28.367
[in English]
Have you told him about the pregnancy?

14:28.450 --> 14:29.451
Eh?

14:29.869 --> 14:31.036
The boy responsible,

14:33.789 --> 14:36.750
[in Yoruba]
Yes, I told him, I went to see him,

14:36.834 --> 14:39.670
If you see the way he treated me,

14:39.753 --> 14:42.715
He insulted me,

14:42.798 --> 14:47.344
my children and my family,

14:47.428 --> 14:51.473
He belittled my daughter,,,

14:52.766 --> 14:55.227
after humiliating her,

14:57.646 --> 14:58.647
Please save me,

14:59.231 --> 15:04.570
Mama,,, are you sure he's the one?

15:05.946 --> 15:07.239
He's the one,

15:07.907 --> 15:11.535
If you want me to swear
in my child's name,

15:12.244 --> 15:16.248
My child is very naive,

15:16.874 --> 15:21.253
That's why he took advantage of her

15:21.754 --> 15:24.048
He has totally destroyed her life,

15:24.131 --> 15:28.469
Mama, it's okay,
Tears are not allowed here,

15:28.552 --> 15:29.929
Take it easy

15:30.012 --> 15:31.096
[speaks Yoruba]

15:36.477 --> 15:37.811
Mama,

15:37.895 --> 15:41.315
[in Yoruba]
I'm listening, King, I'm all ears,

15:41.398 --> 15:44.151
-Mama,
-[in Yoruba] I'm answering you,

15:44.234 --> 15:45.819
[in English]
I have a question for you,

15:49.114 --> 15:54.536
I want you to think carefully
before you answer me,

15:55.204 --> 15:56.956
[in Yoruba]
Please explain, Explain in detail,

15:57.623 --> 15:59.375
[in Yoruba]
I have question for you,

16:01.919 --> 16:03.671
A week from today,,,

16:07.341 --> 16:08.717
the young man,,,

16:10.970 --> 16:12.471
and your child,,,

16:15.224 --> 16:17.059
do you want them to get married?

16:19.728 --> 16:25.651
Or do you want to hear news of his death?

16:28.696 --> 16:29.905
Which do you prefer?

16:30.906 --> 16:32.074
What did you just say?

16:32.658 --> 16:35.703
[in English]
I will not repeat myself,

16:41.792 --> 16:43.919
[in Yoruba]
Ah, what a pity

16:44.545 --> 16:48.382
What a pity, This man disgraced me,

16:49.008 --> 16:54.096
He disgraced and humiliated me!
But it won't go that way,

16:54.179 --> 16:57.558
[in English]
Mama, You have not answered my question,

16:58.350 --> 16:59.393
[in Yoruba]
Is that so?

17:03.272 --> 17:04.982
King,,,

17:05.065 --> 17:10.612
The deed has been done,

17:10.695 --> 17:12.781
What else?

17:12.865 --> 17:16.492
It's marriage,

17:22.458 --> 17:24.084
-Ade,
-Yes, King,

17:25.419 --> 17:29.089
[in English] Take mama outside,
get all the information needed,

17:30.340 --> 17:36.013
I personally, want you
to sort this out immediately,

17:36.096 --> 17:37.389
-Yes, King,
-Thank you,

17:37.473 --> 17:38.640
Mama, this way,

17:38.724 --> 17:40.392
-No need to thank me,
-Thank you,

17:40.476 --> 17:42.269
Mama, no need to thank me,

17:42.352 --> 17:44.146
-Ah, I have to, It is needed,
-[Ade] Mama,

17:44.229 --> 17:46.565
I just want to thank you,
Thank you,

17:46.648 --> 17:50.527
-Don't worry,
-[sighing]

17:50.611 --> 17:52.821
-This way,
-See my life, Thank you,

17:52.905 --> 17:53.906
Market woman!

17:55.157 --> 17:56.909
I'm answering you, King,

17:57.534 --> 17:59.536
A week from now,,,

18:02.164 --> 18:03.999
there will be an election,

18:07.419 --> 18:08.921
Your living things,,,

18:11.381 --> 18:13.217
and the non-living things,,,

18:15.385 --> 18:16.512
male,,,

18:18.514 --> 18:20.015
female,,,

18:21.642 --> 18:24.478
they vote or not,,, we will win,

18:24.561 --> 18:30.150
King, you can't send a gossip
on an errand and she won't deliver,

18:30.943 --> 18:32.236
What you just said,,,

18:32.820 --> 18:36.365
The young, old, male, female,,,

18:36.448 --> 18:42.371
In fact, the whole market belongs to you,

18:44.373 --> 18:46.208
You are in!

18:46.291 --> 18:47.876
[laughing]

18:58.679 --> 19:00.848
Do we still have people outside?

19:01.431 --> 19:03.433
All the way down the street, mum,

19:05.102 --> 19:06.103
Are you okay?

19:06.186 --> 19:07.521
I'm tired,

19:09.356 --> 19:10.816
I'm done for the day, baby,

19:10.899 --> 19:12.442
[in Yoruba]
Sorry,

19:12.526 --> 19:16.613
Please take money, share it among them
for their transportation and food,

19:17.614 --> 19:20.159
-Hmm?
-Okay, Don't worry, mum, I'll handle it,

19:20.617 --> 19:21.910
Thank you, baby,

19:31.003 --> 19:32.754
[woman] This is the one
I was telling you about, ma,

19:32.838 --> 19:35.257
It will make you stand out very well,

19:35.340 --> 19:37.384
It's very pretty, Mummy, see,

19:37.467 --> 19:41.555
Mmm, yes, It's fine, but,,,

19:41.638 --> 19:42.848
[in Yoruba] It's very expensive,

19:42.931 --> 19:45.517
-Please let me look at something else,
-[in Yoruba] Please don't say that,

19:45.601 --> 19:48.729
You shall eat whatever you desire
You shall drink whatever you desire

19:48.812 --> 19:50.522
You shall wear whatever you desire,
by God's grace,

19:50.606 --> 19:53.442
[in English] Just tell God, it is done,
Are you the bride?

19:53.525 --> 19:54.943
-Yes, ma,
-Come here,

19:57.905 --> 19:59.156
You are beautiful,

19:59.781 --> 20:03.243
[in Yoruba] Ma'am! How many times
will your daughter have a wedding?

20:03.327 --> 20:04.536
It's just once,

20:04.620 --> 20:09.333
You have to make your in-laws see
that your child is as precious as gold

20:09.416 --> 20:11.293
and she's not ordinary,

20:11.376 --> 20:12.377
Do you understand me?

20:12.461 --> 20:15.297
-I understand but--
-There are no buts!

20:15.380 --> 20:17.049
There are no buts in your life,

20:17.132 --> 20:18.342
Give it to me

20:18.425 --> 20:20.969
There are no buts in your life,
Can you come closer, my darling?

20:21.053 --> 20:22.721
I will show you something,

20:22.804 --> 20:26.892
[in English] Give me your hand,
Your beautiful hand, [chuckles]

20:27.184 --> 20:28.352
Just look at this,

20:28.435 --> 20:30.938
[in Yoruba]
Ma'am, take a look, Give me your hand,

20:31.021 --> 20:33.440
Feel that, Run it though,

20:33.523 --> 20:34.524
Wow,

20:34.608 --> 20:35.776
Feel that?

20:36.360 --> 20:39.279
Can you feel that? Beautiful,

20:39.363 --> 20:41.657
You see, this was handmade,

20:41.740 --> 20:46.662
Everything you see here was hand-crafted,
It is neck breaking labor,

20:46.745 --> 20:48.497
I know what we're giving you,

20:48.580 --> 20:50.457
[in Yoruba]
May this child benefit from you,

20:50.540 --> 20:52.251
[in English]
Sweetheart, do you like it?

20:52.334 --> 20:54.461
Yes, ma, it does really make my skin pop,

20:54.544 --> 20:56.004
Oh, my God! Pop!

20:56.088 --> 21:00.467
[in Yoruba] You've got it spot on!
Your daughter wants this badly,

21:00.550 --> 21:02.970
-You know what is good!
-Good afternoon, ma,

21:03.220 --> 21:05.806
Ah, Can you please go into my office?

21:05.889 --> 21:08.392
When I'm done with my customer,
I'll meet you in a minute, okay?

21:08.475 --> 21:10.185
-Okay, ma,
-Thank you,

21:10.269 --> 21:13.230
[in Yoruba] Ah, thank you, my dear,
What were we talking about?

21:13.313 --> 21:15.107
Let me tell you something,

21:15.190 --> 21:17.693
If you have money that
covers the entire world

21:17.776 --> 21:19.653
and you don't spend it on your child,

21:19.736 --> 21:21.071
It's all a waste,

21:21.154 --> 21:23.573
If we die today,
will the money be buried with us?

21:24.533 --> 21:25.659
No,

21:25.742 --> 21:27.160
Do you see this child?

21:27.244 --> 21:29.329
I'm tapping into your grace,

21:29.413 --> 21:32.291
I have two children, A boy and a girl,

21:32.916 --> 21:36.128
And I am praying for a day like this,

21:36.211 --> 21:39.089
I am praying for both a son-in-law
and a daughter-in-law,

21:39.172 --> 21:42.384
So because of that, I will sow
into your daughter's wedding,

21:42.467 --> 21:43.844
-Huh?
-Yes,

21:43.927 --> 21:47.597
I know how much I bought this fabric
and I know what my profit should be,

21:47.681 --> 21:52.644
My profit is 5% and I'll take it off,
Just pay the cost price

21:53.061 --> 21:54.938
[in English]
Thank you so very much, madam,

21:55.689 --> 21:58.650
You see, I didn't come
expecting to spend that much,

21:58.734 --> 22:00.694
[in Yoruba]
Ah, what are you talking about?

22:00.777 --> 22:03.447
If that's the situation,
I have a POS machine,

22:03.530 --> 22:04.573
Bring the machine!

22:04.656 --> 22:07.951
You see, this store is yours,

22:08.035 --> 22:10.120
Come in and take whatever you want,
Do you understand?

22:10.203 --> 22:12.122
Now I know you, and we've become family,
Do you understand?

22:12.205 --> 22:16.626
[in English] Just make her happy,
Make her happy, please,

22:17.377 --> 22:18.378
Okay,

22:19.254 --> 22:20.756
Thank you, Mummy,

22:20.839 --> 22:23.592
Well done, well done,

22:23.675 --> 22:25.052
I pray you enjoy it,

22:25.135 --> 22:26.762
[in Yoruba]
God will make it a day of joy for you,

22:26.845 --> 22:29.890
Fantastic!
Unfortunately, I have to leave you,

22:29.973 --> 22:31.433
I need to attend to the other guest,

22:31.516 --> 22:34.436
Nneka, the shoe and bag,
don't forget to show them,

22:36.480 --> 22:37.606
Shoe and bag?

22:41.568 --> 22:44.362
-[in Pidgin] Boss, you know what happened?
-What happened?

22:44.446 --> 22:47.699
That's what I was expecting from you!
You have just been,,,

22:47.783 --> 22:50.660
So, Boss,
as I tried to position myself,

22:50.744 --> 22:51.787
Do you understand me?

22:51.870 --> 22:54.664
Oh, God, Bosco, speak,

22:54.748 --> 22:57.459
It hurts that you guys
weren't there to see what I did,

22:58.043 --> 22:59.753
As soon as I charged,,,

22:59.836 --> 23:03.465
they just kept looking at me and started
bringing out their guns and grenades,

23:03.548 --> 23:04.966
[hip-hop playing]

23:05.050 --> 23:08.095
I didn't have any weapons with me,
but I stood my ground firmly,

23:08.178 --> 23:10.931
The weed I was smoking before
I left you guys just kicked into action

23:11.014 --> 23:13.100
and everything switched to slow motion,

23:13.183 --> 23:15.894
Then I attacked, and ten people fell,

23:18.730 --> 23:21.650
As one tried to hit me in the chest,
I countered the attack,

23:21.733 --> 23:22.984
Then I hit him again,

23:23.068 --> 23:25.070
Before I realized it,
the 50 men were on the floor,

23:25.153 --> 23:26.780
I didn't even have a scratch,
Boss, take a look,

23:26.863 --> 23:28.240
-Bosco,
-That's me,

23:28.323 --> 23:30.659
The person who talks too much
will definitely tell tall tales,

23:31.993 --> 23:32.994
Don't be upset, boss,

23:33.078 --> 23:34.412
[music stops]

23:37.207 --> 23:38.208
Hey!

23:38.291 --> 23:41.962
-Odogwu Malay!
-My people, I salute,

23:42.045 --> 23:44.548
Maka Bariga, Baddest,

23:44.631 --> 23:47.676
-My G,
-Baddest, baddest, baddest, What's new?

23:47.759 --> 23:49.553
-I'm good
-You're just shining,

23:49.636 --> 23:50.887
What's up?

23:50.971 --> 23:53.765
-Men everywhere,
-That's right, that's right,

23:54.349 --> 23:57.352
Now you've appeared in our hood,
are we safe?

23:57.435 --> 24:00.397
They say if a monkey puts on his sneakers
and steps into the hood,

24:00.480 --> 24:02.023
there must be a mission,

24:02.107 --> 24:05.235
I have something for you,
You'll like what I brought,

24:05.318 --> 24:10.490
Let's just convert here
into a small office, quickly,

24:13.201 --> 24:14.661
So, what's up?

24:14.744 --> 24:18.540
I just got back from Anambra,

24:18.623 --> 24:21.835
My boys over there
got some serious intel for us,

24:21.918 --> 24:25.463
Remember my little brother, Dile?

24:25.547 --> 24:31.845
Dile is really close
to one of Ebele's boys here in Lagos,

24:31.928 --> 24:38.393
So, Dile told me that the man
has about 10 million in his house,

24:39.561 --> 24:41.271
I was shocked, my brother,

24:41.354 --> 24:42.564
10 million Naira?

24:42.647 --> 24:46.109
What's up with you, Makanaki?
10 million Naira?

24:46.193 --> 24:49.696
Did stealing 10 million Naira
get us where we are? 10 million dollars!

24:51.239 --> 24:52.240
In a safe?

24:52.324 --> 24:55.243
No way, Those types
don't put money in safes anymore,

24:55.327 --> 24:58.663
The bastard buried the money
in a septic tank,

24:58.747 --> 25:02.167
You know this whistle-blowing thing
is opening doors like crazy,

25:02.250 --> 25:05.921
Put some money in the hands of these
little boys and they'll start snitching,

25:06.630 --> 25:09.466
The government gives five percent,
but we give 10 percent, that's it,

25:09.549 --> 25:11.384
Makanaki, you totally get it,

25:11.468 --> 25:13.511
I even have bigger intel for you, Maka,

25:13.595 --> 25:16.514
You know Number One?
You know, Aare Akinwande,

25:16.598 --> 25:18.642
Same thing, same thing, my guy,

25:18.725 --> 25:22.062
So, if you have all this info,
why did you bring it to me?

25:22.145 --> 25:27.817
Because, Odogwu, I know you very well,
You're not Santa Claus,

25:27.901 --> 25:31.112
-Why did you bring this deal to me?
-Maka, you're still learning,

25:31.196 --> 25:36.534
Maka, I'm a businessman,
Fifteen percent of zero is zero, you know,

25:36.618 --> 25:40.538
Here's what I want us to do, Makanaki,
I want us to work together,

25:40.622 --> 25:44.376
I'm proposing a partnership,
Let's work together,

25:44.459 --> 25:47.045
Let's get in there and clear out
this money from all three locations,

25:47.128 --> 25:51.716
Maka, this cash will change our lives,
Everything,

25:51.800 --> 25:55.011
If you think we're balling right now,
this is where the real balling starts,

25:56.012 --> 25:57.389
I'm telling you,

25:58.890 --> 26:00.308
Fifty-fifty?

26:00.392 --> 26:02.811
Yeah, You're my nigga, so fifty-fifty,

26:02.894 --> 26:05.689
But that's after we have paid
40% to the King,

26:05.772 --> 26:09.276
-Who? What's she doing in this deal?
-Maka, you surprise me,

26:09.359 --> 26:12.195
-What is her role in this deal?
-Odogwu, please,

26:12.279 --> 26:16.533
Her 40% must get to her
whether she's involved in the deal or not,

26:16.616 --> 26:18.952
Let's just pay her share
and keep what's ours,

26:19.035 --> 26:20.954
Please, This person in question,

26:21.037 --> 26:24.416
When was the last time
she brought anything to the table?

26:24.499 --> 26:26.126
But she still eats from what we catch,

26:27.085 --> 26:29.129
Odogwu, you won't open your eyes,

26:29.879 --> 26:31.715
-But let's talk,
-Okay,

26:35.385 --> 26:36.761
[in English]
What are you telling me?

26:37.387 --> 26:39.306
Aare went back on his promise,

26:39.389 --> 26:42.017
So what are you doing here?

26:43.226 --> 26:46.271
Because I'm not a minister,

26:46.730 --> 26:50.942
[scoffs] I am not a deputy governor,
not even a bloody commissioner!

26:51.026 --> 26:55.030
-Mum, calm down,
-"Calm down?" Ha!

26:55.113 --> 26:57.741
The governor just wants you to know
that he tried his best, ma,

26:57.824 --> 27:00.869
Can you listen
to what this fool is telling me?

27:00.952 --> 27:02.996
Listen to what this fool is saying to me!

27:03.079 --> 27:05.081
So my money, my dollars,

27:05.165 --> 27:08.376
all the money spent
on this bastard election was for nothing?

27:08.460 --> 27:11.296
It's not like that, ma,
We really appreciate all you've done,

27:11.379 --> 27:14.716
Then what exactly happened, Taiwo?
This was a done deal,

27:14.799 --> 27:16.885
-Ha!
-Can I speak freely?

27:16.968 --> 27:18.053
Speak,

27:18.136 --> 27:22.140
Okay, Seems some of the party members
are worried about,,,

27:22.766 --> 27:24.017
your reputation, ma,

27:28.396 --> 27:31.066
What? My reputation?

27:32.609 --> 27:34.319
[in Yoruba]
It will not be well with you,

27:34.402 --> 27:37.447
[in English]
You are mad, My reputation,

27:38.698 --> 27:42.160
So when I was financing the movement,
nobody spoke about reputation,

27:42.243 --> 27:44.412
-Mum, calm down,
-Don't tell me to calm down,

27:44.496 --> 27:48.458
Aare wants to talk about reputation,
Oh, ho! So, I'm the fool!

27:48.541 --> 27:51.211
The moron that was doing
their dirty work for them!

27:53.254 --> 27:59.219
I will send you to Aare,
Tell Aare that I, Eniola,

28:00.637 --> 28:03.223
will take all my money,

28:03.306 --> 28:07.143
All my blood, drop for drop,

28:07.227 --> 28:09.813
-Ma?
-Hey! Can you imagine?

28:10.688 --> 28:15.735
They can't even come themselves,
They sent you rat, to sit in my chair,

28:15.819 --> 28:18.279
I think it's time you leave, Mr, Onitiri,

28:20.698 --> 28:21.825
[sighs]

28:30.291 --> 28:33.461
[man] Mama, Excuse me, ma,

28:33.545 --> 28:34.546
Huh?

28:36.423 --> 28:38.174
[man] Makanaki on the phone, ma,

28:40.510 --> 28:41.553
What is it?

28:41.636 --> 28:43.388
[man] Makanaki, on the phone,

28:43.888 --> 28:45.098
What does he want?

28:45.181 --> 28:50.812
Listen, I am tired
and I am not ready for his trouble now,

28:50.895 --> 28:52.272
-Ma?
-Hmm?

28:52.355 --> 28:54.232
It seems very, very important,

29:03.032 --> 29:04.325
-Korede,
-Mama,

29:04.409 --> 29:06.828
[in Yoruba] Good evening, ma,
It's Makanaki speaking,

29:06.911 --> 29:10.957
-Yes, what is it? How are you?
-Fine, thank you, ma,

29:11.541 --> 29:14.169
[in English] We need to see you,
We have urgent things to talk about,

29:14.252 --> 29:16.337
-What is it?
-Business,

29:16.921 --> 29:18.715
Ah, What kind of business?

29:18.798 --> 29:19.883
[scoffs]

29:20.967 --> 29:24.179
[in Yoruba] Mama, it is wrong
to use parables on elders,

29:24.262 --> 29:25.889
What other business do we discuss?

29:26.306 --> 29:28.141
Please, we need to meet,

29:32.145 --> 29:35.648
[in English]
Korede, listen to me and listen good,

29:36.316 --> 29:39.027
I have enough on my plate

29:39.110 --> 29:42.238
to get involved
with your small, small play,

29:42.322 --> 29:43.823
Just do the needful,

29:44.532 --> 29:48.203
[in Yoruba]
No ill wind must touch my people,

29:49.871 --> 29:51.164
Do you understand?

29:52.499 --> 29:54.876
Pay me my tax, finish,

29:55.919 --> 29:58.922
Other than that, I don't care,

30:01.424 --> 30:02.467
-Take this,
-Yes, ma,

30:02.550 --> 30:04.010
Thank you,

30:07.597 --> 30:09.766
-[man] Gobir,
-Attention, sir!

30:11.601 --> 30:14.604
I hope that you're finding
everything satisfactory,

30:15.522 --> 30:18.775
-Yes, sir, Fine, Really fine, sir,
-That's good,

30:20.735 --> 30:21.945
Nice, isn't it?

30:22.987 --> 30:24.697
Very nice, Very nice, sir,

30:25.073 --> 30:27.909
A gift from my new son-in-law,

30:28.993 --> 30:30.662
-Amazing,
-Yeah,

30:30.745 --> 30:31.955
Let's get to it, sit down,

30:32.038 --> 30:33.248
Thank you, sir,

30:36.584 --> 30:39.462
You will not believe
who we have in custody,

30:41.422 --> 30:43.049
-Who's that?
-Eigbe,

30:43.466 --> 30:45.218
-Eigbe?
-And Rewane,

30:45.301 --> 30:46.678
Ebele Rewane?

30:46.761 --> 30:48.263
Senator Rewane,

30:49.138 --> 30:50.348
Wow!

30:50.431 --> 30:54.853
Both of them were using
the National Petroleum Corporation

30:54.936 --> 31:00.275
as a personal treasury, removing
millions of dollars without conscience,

31:00.358 --> 31:04.112
Anyway, they are both yours right now,

31:05.613 --> 31:08.908
-I want you to take their statements,
-Okay, sir,

31:08.992 --> 31:12.078
Make the necessary
residence verifications,

31:12.161 --> 31:14.747
-Yes, sir,
-The press will be here anytime soon,

31:14.831 --> 31:15.957
Okay, sir,

31:18.167 --> 31:21.546
How is your wife, Hauwa? I heard--

31:21.629 --> 31:24.090
[in Hausa]
Much better now, sir, No problem,

31:24.173 --> 31:26.259
She's much better now,

31:26.342 --> 31:29.178
[in English]
In case you need anything, do let me know,

31:30.305 --> 31:31.306
Okay, sir, I will,

31:35.602 --> 31:36.853
[sighs]

31:39.731 --> 31:41.608
